description:
## Context
Investigation found 498 broken link references across all PSEO pages due to 5 URLs that don't exist or point to wrong locations.

## Broken URLs
1. `/checker/` ‚Üí 249 references (should redirect to `/`)
2. `/citation-checker/` ‚Üí 195 references (should redirect to `/`)
3. `/generator/` ‚Üí 15 references (homepage IS the generator, redirect to `/`)
4. `/tools/style-comparison/` ‚Üí 15 references (page exists at `/guide/apa-vs-mla-vs-chicago/`)
5. `/guides/` ‚Üí 249 references (will be fixed by separate issue creating this page)

## Solution
Add nginx redirects to `/opt/citations/deployment/nginx/citations.conf`:

```nginx
# Fix broken navigation links
location = /checker/ {
    return 301 /;
}

location = /citation-checker/ {
    return 301 /;
}

location = /generator/ {
    return 301 /;
}

location = /tools/style-comparison/ {
    return 301 /guide/apa-vs-mla-vs-chicago/;
}
```

## Deployment
1. Update nginx config
2. Test config: `sudo nginx -t`
3. Reload: `sudo systemctl reload nginx`
4. Verify redirects work

## Regeneration Required
‚ùå NO - nginx config changes only

## Impact
Fixes 249 broken links immediately (498 total after guides page is created)
